Update 217 confirms that the Southern Hemisphere seasonal influenza epidemic is well underway. No novel strains have appeared with variable predominance of existing types and with A(H3N2) predominating. Exceptionally, this update reports that in Chile respiratory syncytial virus accounted for 72 percent of the positive respiratory samples followed by influenza at only 12 percent. The main circulating influenza virus has been influenza A(H3N2). - Mod.CP]
